--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages psmisc.

The psmisc package contains utilities for managing processes on your system:
pstree, killall and fuser. The pstree command displays a tree structure of all
of the running processes on your system. The killall command sends a specified
signal (SIGTERM if nothing is specified) to processes identified by name.
The fuser command identifies the PIDs of processes that are using specified
files or filesystems.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: psmisc
       psmisc_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: psmisc
       psmisc_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  psmisc_state
    Specify predetermined 'psmisc_state' variable (string).
    Notice: 'psmisc' is a core package and can therefore not be removed.

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
